11
00:01:56,009 --> 00:01:58,000
Lula needs to be taught a lesson!

12
00:01:58,769 --> 00:02:01,920
Whatever's happened...

13
00:02:02,089 --> 00:02:04,364
...it's not for you to decide,
you little shit!

14
00:02:04,849 --> 00:02:08,080
-Dagger!
-Dagger's gonna die!

15
00:02:08,449 --> 00:02:11,725
-Gonna die!
-Calm down!

16
00:02:14,049 --> 00:02:17,644
You think you're gonna decide this?
Come on, then, I'm ready.

17
00:02:19,129 --> 00:02:21,768
-What's this?
-Gonna die! Gonna die!

18
00:02:22,769 --> 00:02:25,761
Like I said, I've got no one
waiting for me on the outside.

19
00:02:25,969 --> 00:02:28,005
I'm in no hurry to get out.

20
00:02:28,169 --> 00:02:29,966
Anyone wants a fight,
let's get on with it.

21
00:02:30,129 --> 00:02:32,279
I'll crush all of you.

22
00:02:35,169 --> 00:02:38,684
What the fuck's wrong with you guys?!
Let's cool it here!

23
00:02:39,769 --> 00:02:41,600
What's going on, Dagger?

24
00:02:41,769 --> 00:02:45,125
-Lula attacked me from behind, Ebony.
-He's a badass!

25
00:02:45,289 --> 00:02:47,678
He went for Dagger from behind!

26
00:02:47,969 --> 00:02:49,482
Right out of line, man!

27
00:02:50,209 --> 00:02:51,608
Gonna die!

28
00:02:52,009 --> 00:02:53,567
Gonna die!

29
00:03:01,289 --> 00:03:04,964
-You locking me in there, Ebony?
-First get in there, then speak!

30
00:03:06,529 --> 00:03:09,202
-Don't throw Dagger in here, Ebony.
-We don't want trouble.

31
00:03:09,369 --> 00:03:10,882
Step away, damn it!

32
00:03:12,009 --> 00:03:14,728
So? I'm all ears.

33
00:03:15,129 --> 00:03:17,006
How come he's so mad at you?

34
00:03:17,169 --> 00:03:18,761
You heard.

35
00:03:18,929 --> 00:03:22,046
Lula came out of nowhere with a knife
and tried to kill me.

36
00:03:22,209 --> 00:03:23,528
I dodged.

37
00:03:23,689 --> 00:03:27,045
We scuffled till they broke us up.

38
00:03:27,689 --> 00:03:30,078
The rest you know.

39
00:03:45,929 --> 00:03:47,157
Good morning, Mr. Pires.

40
00:03:48,169 --> 00:03:51,445
I do apologize for this
disgusting behavior...

41
00:03:51,769 --> 00:03:55,808
...which has invaded our household
today.

42
00:03:57,569 --> 00:04:03,280
Only this idiot Lula,
a young, inexperienced con...

43
00:04:03,769 --> 00:04:07,967
...suddenly got this attitude,
without even asking permission!

44
00:04:08,129 --> 00:04:10,802
Dagger killed my father!
He killed my father!

45
00:04:10,969 --> 00:04:12,880
I sure did, kid.

46
00:04:13,049 --> 00:04:16,803
And not only him,
I've killed plenty more besides.

47
00:04:16,969 --> 00:04:20,723
Ebony! Mr. Pires!
Dagger killed my father...

48
00:04:20,889 --> 00:04:24,325
...in front of my mother.
He's been telling everyone!

49
00:04:24,489 --> 00:04:28,323
You gonna deny that, asshole?!
Are you gonna deny it? Are you?

50
00:04:28,489 --> 00:04:31,003
-Ebony, please.
-What?

51
00:04:31,169 --> 00:04:33,444
Tell the kid he doesn't know
half the story.

52
00:04:33,609 --> 00:04:36,760
-lf he did....
-Son of a bitch! I'll kill you!

53
00:04:37,329 --> 00:04:41,686
Tell him to ask his mother if she
was really as upset as all that.

54
00:04:41,929 --> 00:04:45,683
Or was it a relief when I came
and grabbed his belt from him?

55
00:04:45,849 --> 00:04:47,362
Lies! That's a lie!

56
00:04:47,529 --> 00:04:51,238
Like hell it is! I saw it for myself.

57
00:04:53,289 --> 00:04:55,644
He'd have thrashed her to death.

58
00:04:59,609 --> 00:05:04,239
I thought you'd have heard
by now, kid!

59
00:05:07,489 --> 00:05:10,640
Your mother paid me
to kill your father.

60
00:05:11,609 --> 00:05:13,565
Get it now?

61
00:05:14,889 --> 00:05:16,641
It was your mother who wiped him out!

62
00:05:41,969 --> 00:05:43,163
Hear that?

63
00:05:46,569 --> 00:05:47,718
He's calmed down!

64
00:05:57,609 --> 00:05:59,008
He's calmed down!

65
00:06:00,689 --> 00:06:03,078
I want them both out here
in their underwear.

66
00:06:30,249 --> 00:06:34,765
Lula, as far as I'm concerned,
we're quits.

67
00:06:39,689 --> 00:06:41,122
Let's forget it, shall we?

68
00:06:46,529 --> 00:06:51,125
You've put me to shame, and on
the day of the doctor's first visit.

69
00:06:58,489 --> 00:07:01,606
So, Lula, what brought
you back in here?

70
00:07:01,769 --> 00:07:03,327
I left here...

71
00:07:03,489 --> 00:07:06,561
...went home and found
my wife in bed with someone else.

72
00:07:06,729 --> 00:07:09,243
The son of a bitch had the nerve
to tell me, "That's life."

73
00:07:09,409 --> 00:07:11,764
I shot him three times just
to prove the contrary.

74
00:07:11,929 --> 00:07:16,207
You should know that whatever
goes on outside gets settled outside.

75
00:07:17,609 --> 00:07:21,682
In here, anyone who behaves
knows we'll do what we can...

76
00:07:21,849 --> 00:07:26,764
...to show him the front door,
where his family is waiting.

77
00:07:27,369 --> 00:07:31,408
But anyone who's proud of being
a criminal, with blood in his eye...

78
00:07:32,529 --> 00:07:35,839
...we'll do everything to
prolong his life in here.

79
00:07:36,889 --> 00:07:39,687
We usually forget people
like that in here.

80
00:07:45,289 --> 00:07:47,519
Doctor, this is Ebony.

81
00:07:51,929 --> 00:07:55,160
Yes, doctor,
Ebony's got a problem.

82
00:07:56,129 --> 00:07:58,882
My kitchen knife is still missing.

83
00:08:00,049 --> 00:08:02,609
Whoever took it,
I'll give you one chance.

84
00:08:03,369 --> 00:08:07,647
Return it or there'll be
one prisoner dead every day!

85
00:08:09,049 --> 00:08:12,041
I'd like to ask our visitors
to turn their backs...

86
00:08:12,809 --> 00:08:15,528
...since there's an ashamed
crook present.

87
00:08:16,609 --> 00:08:20,045
But when I turn around...

88
00:08:20,569 --> 00:08:23,037
...I sure would like to see that knife.

89
00:08:25,129 --> 00:08:27,085
I'll count to three.

90
00:08:27,529 --> 00:08:29,008
One...

91
00:08:29,369 --> 00:08:30,882
...two....

92
00:08:31,449 --> 00:08:33,121
I'm turning.

93
00:08:36,169 --> 00:08:37,443
Three.

94
00:08:45,769 --> 00:08:48,078
-From your kitchen?
-Yes, sir.

95
00:08:49,769 --> 00:08:54,001
This is the yellow wing, doctor,
because they're afraid.

96
00:08:54,169 --> 00:08:56,319
It's like a jail within the jail.

97
00:08:56,489 --> 00:08:59,367
They're locked up here for their
own safety. They're scared.

98
00:08:59,529 --> 00:09:03,408
Career killers, rapists,
stool pigeons, bad payers.

99
00:09:03,569 --> 00:09:05,799
In here, you know,
prisoners never forgive.

100
00:09:05,969 --> 00:09:09,279
Mr. Pires, don't these people
ever get sun? It's so musty!

101
00:09:13,209 --> 00:09:15,006
Anyone want to go outside?

102
00:09:15,169 --> 00:09:19,048
Take a walk in the yard?
Get some fresh air?

103
00:09:33,329 --> 00:09:37,447
-What do these people do all day?
-They come and go all day long...

104
00:09:37,609 --> 00:09:40,601
...think they're busy,
but it gets them nowhere.

105
00:09:40,969 --> 00:09:43,847
Doctor, 7000 men in jail!

106
00:09:44,009 --> 00:09:46,284
There are 1800
in this pavilion alone.

107
00:09:46,849 --> 00:09:50,637
If they knew how AIDS is spread,
that would already help.

108
00:09:50,809 --> 00:09:55,405
They catch the disease and have sex,
so there's no stopping the epidemic.

109
00:09:55,569 --> 00:09:59,084
The only ones who'll listen to your
advice are the really smart ones...

110
00:09:59,249 --> 00:10:02,639
...who only want to get out alive
in order to keep robbing.

111
00:10:02,809 --> 00:10:03,958
That's their whole life.

112
00:10:04,129 --> 00:10:07,838
Maybe. But they're living
at the center of the disease.

113
00:10:09,089 --> 00:10:11,239
-They're the prisoners here.
-Prisoners?

114
00:10:11,529 --> 00:10:15,568
They own this cell. This place doesn't
explode because they don't want it to.

115
00:10:16,089 --> 00:10:18,000
God bless you, child.

116
00:10:20,049 --> 00:10:22,085
I didn't know you had a family.

117
00:10:24,009 --> 00:10:26,921
I thought I'd lost it.

118
00:10:27,129 --> 00:10:28,926
My whole life in jail...

119
00:10:29,089 --> 00:10:31,045
...but even so I raised 18 kids...

120
00:10:31,209 --> 00:10:33,848
...and not one of them has even been
near a police station.

121
00:10:34,249 --> 00:10:36,763
That girl, my youngest...

122
00:10:36,969 --> 00:10:39,199
...she said she doesn't remember
my face...

123
00:10:39,369 --> 00:10:41,280
...so she's decided to come and visit.

124
00:10:42,089 --> 00:10:47,686
I'd like you to authorize me to see her.

125
00:10:47,849 --> 00:10:50,886
I don't want my daughter
around all the scum.

126
00:10:51,369 --> 00:10:53,485
That's going to be tricky.

127
00:10:53,649 --> 00:10:56,209
What if the 7000 others
ask me the same thing?

128
00:10:58,129 --> 00:10:59,608
Excuse me.

129
00:11:05,489 --> 00:11:06,524
Good morning.

130
00:11:15,009 --> 00:11:16,647
Hey, what's up?

131
00:11:24,369 --> 00:11:28,920
Need anything, doctor?
Coffee, sugar, chocolate, toothpaste?

132
00:11:29,129 --> 00:11:31,962
Joints are only two packs
of Marlboros each. Want one?

133
00:11:32,129 --> 00:11:33,562
I don't smoke.

134
00:11:33,729 --> 00:11:37,563
Too bad! Commerce, doctor!
Makes the world go round!

135
00:11:42,529 --> 00:11:43,564
Let's go.

136
00:11:45,289 --> 00:11:46,847
Easy, now. That's it.

137
00:11:49,889 --> 00:11:51,242
Slow.

138
00:11:55,169 --> 00:11:56,841
He can't spit there.

139
00:11:57,209 --> 00:12:00,121
Tuberculosis. Anyone steps
on that, spreads the disease.

140
00:12:00,649 --> 00:12:04,642
If he had the strength,
he'd go to the sink.

141
00:12:05,769 --> 00:12:07,248
It's not easy.

142
00:12:08,329 --> 00:12:09,887
He must be isolated.

143
00:12:11,689 --> 00:12:13,122
But where, doctor?

144
00:12:20,209 --> 00:12:21,164
Name?

145
00:12:21,329 --> 00:12:23,559
Everyone calls me the Beard.

146
00:12:25,729 --> 00:12:27,128
Why are you here?

147
00:12:28,129 --> 00:12:29,164
Well...

148
00:12:29,729 --> 00:12:31,526
...my brother was killed.

149
00:12:32,249 --> 00:12:36,720
Two days later, the murderer
had a little meeting with death...

150
00:12:37,289 --> 00:12:39,849
...so suspicions fell upon my
good self.

151
00:12:40,409 --> 00:12:45,802
Some said I did it and others came
along and said they saw it wasn't me.

152
00:12:46,209 --> 00:12:49,963
With some saying it was me
and others saying not...

153
00:12:50,129 --> 00:12:54,919
...here I am, five years now,
waiting for the judge to decide.

154
00:12:55,849 --> 00:12:59,762
Do you have sex here in jail?

155
00:13:01,049 --> 00:13:04,325
-Anyone who denies that is a liar.
-Use condoms?

156
00:13:04,889 --> 00:13:06,641
If I've got one, I do.

157
00:13:06,969 --> 00:13:09,437
-IV drugs?
-How dare you, doctor?

158
00:13:09,609 --> 00:13:12,919
I wonder, Beard!
What's that mark on your arm?

159
00:13:19,169 --> 00:13:20,841
Beard is next!

160
00:13:35,769 --> 00:13:37,168
My name's Alipio.

161
00:13:39,729 --> 00:13:41,287
Do you use drugs?

162
00:13:42,489 --> 00:13:43,842
Needles?

163
00:13:44,009 --> 00:13:48,639
No way, doctor. I got AIDS from
all the ass I've had in jail.

164
00:13:49,849 --> 00:13:51,123
Plenty of ass.

165
00:13:54,289 --> 00:13:56,280
Is it still worth taking the test?

166
00:14:00,009 --> 00:14:02,569
I listen, give advice...

167
00:14:02,729 --> 00:14:05,243
...a little tenderness,
hold them tight...

168
00:14:05,929 --> 00:14:08,966
...and then they always give us
something nice in return.

169
00:14:09,129 --> 00:14:13,520
A pack of cigarettes, some candy,
a slice of cheese.

170
00:14:13,769 --> 00:14:17,079
So many men shut up
in here, doctor...

171
00:14:17,249 --> 00:14:20,127
...without our feminine support.

172
00:14:20,289 --> 00:14:22,757
Yeah, I've got AIDS,
but I didn't get it in here.

173
00:14:22,929 --> 00:14:25,648
I brought it in off the streets,
and I can't complain.

174
00:14:25,809 --> 00:14:31,008
You come in here sick and they
treat you with respect, dignity...

175
00:14:31,169 --> 00:14:33,967
...and that's the greatest thing
in a crook's life.

176
00:14:34,129 --> 00:14:35,881
I'm a junkie and a dealer.

177
00:14:36,049 --> 00:14:40,520
In my business, if a guy doesn't
pay up, I can't take back...

178
00:14:40,689 --> 00:14:43,965
...what I sold him. The bastard's
already smoked it, snorted it.

179
00:14:44,569 --> 00:14:46,525
I take whatever he's got.

180
00:14:46,889 --> 00:14:49,449
If he's got nothing, I kill him.

181
00:14:50,889 --> 00:14:54,245
The other day I tried to get
an extra banana from the guy...

182
00:14:54,409 --> 00:14:57,606
...who delivers lunch. The bastard
said only if I kissed his banana.

183
00:14:57,769 --> 00:15:00,158
So what the hell,
I'm just crazy about bananas.

184
00:15:00,329 --> 00:15:03,401
Doctor, everyone in my cell's
got this itch.

185
00:15:03,569 --> 00:15:04,843
It's unbearable.

186
00:15:05,289 --> 00:15:08,122
Scabies. I'll give you some medicine.

187
00:15:09,769 --> 00:15:11,839
So how are you getting along?

188
00:15:12,329 --> 00:15:16,959
Doctor, after shooting cocaine
in the dark with a blunt needle...

189
00:15:17,129 --> 00:15:19,689
...drawing blood with this rig...

190
00:15:19,849 --> 00:15:22,079
...is hardly fair play.

191
00:15:23,809 --> 00:15:25,288
Too bad!

192
00:16:29,289 --> 00:16:30,847
See what you did?

193
00:16:31,489 --> 00:16:33,047
See what you did?

194
00:17:55,009 --> 00:17:56,727
-Who are you?
-I'm the doctor.

195
00:17:56,889 --> 00:17:59,164
I was taking blood samples.

196
00:17:59,329 --> 00:18:01,240
-Just ask--
-Watch out!

197
00:18:01,409 --> 00:18:03,923
Like you have
to tell me who to ask.

198
00:18:04,089 --> 00:18:08,162
I'm calling the duty officer.
Wait here.

199
00:18:08,329 --> 00:18:11,127
If no one can identify you,
you're staying right where you are.

200
00:18:36,449 --> 00:18:39,043
Don't take it personally.
It's their job to escape...

201
00:18:39,289 --> 00:18:40,961
...and mine not to let them.

202
00:18:50,529 --> 00:18:51,678
Doctor!

203
00:18:54,569 --> 00:18:56,002
You coming back?

204
00:19:10,889 --> 00:19:15,838
I knew many of those men hadn't
shown their victims any mercy...

205
00:19:16,009 --> 00:19:18,318
...but society has its judges.

206
00:19:18,489 --> 00:19:20,480
And I wasn't one of them.

207
00:19:20,849 --> 00:19:23,921
At the same time,
what did I have to do with all that?

208
00:19:24,089 --> 00:19:25,966
I had two choices.:

209
00:19:26,129 --> 00:19:28,643
Forget or go back.

210
00:19:30,889 --> 00:19:32,447
Take a deep breath.

211
00:19:35,369 --> 00:19:36,484
Smoker?

212
00:19:36,649 --> 00:19:37,798
Just cigarettes.

213
00:19:38,569 --> 00:19:40,560
-No crack?
-Never.

214
00:19:41,289 --> 00:19:42,722
Sleep well?

215
00:19:43,009 --> 00:19:45,477
Hardly, doctor.
The mind never stops...

216
00:19:45,649 --> 00:19:49,608
...what with one guy trying to settle
a score outside, collecting a debt...

217
00:19:49,769 --> 00:19:53,284
...another trying to dig a tunnel.
And there goes another day.

218
00:19:53,449 --> 00:19:57,442
-You still got much time to do?
-A few more years.

219
00:19:57,769 --> 00:19:59,088
And why did you come here?

220
00:19:59,249 --> 00:20:02,719
-Legitimate self-defense, doctor.
-That lands you in jail nowadays?

221
00:20:02,889 --> 00:20:04,004
It did in my case.

222
00:20:04,169 --> 00:20:07,844
Here's what happened.
It was Christmas...

223
00:20:08,449 --> 00:20:11,043
...the bells ringing,
snow in the windows.

224
00:20:11,569 --> 00:20:16,927
Me, Bristles and Fatso arranged
to do a jewelry store job.

225
00:20:18,849 --> 00:20:22,762
Neat work, doctor.
Never even fired a shot.

226
00:20:23,849 --> 00:20:25,567
The problem was later.

227
00:21:03,369 --> 00:21:05,485
How are we going to split it up?

228
00:21:05,689 --> 00:21:08,157
Fatso and I will make three
piles and you choose first.

229
00:21:11,369 --> 00:21:14,884
Son, not now.
Get out! Go on!

230
00:21:15,369 --> 00:21:16,597
Go on, son!

231
00:21:37,049 --> 00:21:39,199
You fucking moron!

232
00:21:39,849 --> 00:21:42,727
We're splitting the loot and you
come at me with your hand covered?

233
00:21:47,809 --> 00:21:49,606
It's his own fault he died.

234
00:21:52,329 --> 00:21:53,808
What the fuck's going on?

235
00:21:55,369 --> 00:21:57,360
So you shot him in the heat of
the moment...

236
00:21:59,009 --> 00:22:02,524
...but we had agreed for me
to shoot you...

237
00:22:02,889 --> 00:22:04,766
...so we could take your share.

238
00:22:04,929 --> 00:22:06,362
So shoot!

239
00:22:09,969 --> 00:22:11,687
Go on, fire away!

240
00:22:15,689 --> 00:22:17,202
I can't, damn it.

241
00:22:17,849 --> 00:22:19,168
Give me your rod.

242
00:22:24,969 --> 00:22:26,641
Oh, my God!

243
00:22:31,609 --> 00:22:36,478
Being betrayed by your buddy for
nothing, doctor...

244
00:22:36,809 --> 00:22:41,837
...like Judas, the guy who
spat in the face of Jesus.

245
00:22:42,009 --> 00:22:43,886
So how does the story end?

