515
00:45:13,209 --> 00:45:15,848
I can't....

516
00:45:16,009 --> 00:45:17,761
I need...

517
00:45:17,929 --> 00:45:19,840
...to get somewhere safe.

518
00:45:20,329 --> 00:45:23,082
-I don't want to die!
-I'm sorry, doctor.

519
00:45:23,249 --> 00:45:27,720
I'm against the death penalty,
but not for rape.

520
00:45:27,889 --> 00:45:30,005
If you ask me, it's just too bad.

521
00:45:36,769 --> 00:45:37,918
So that's it, doctor.

522
00:46:15,929 --> 00:46:18,443
Come on, old man. It's past lockdown.

523
00:46:39,529 --> 00:46:40,962
Get a move on!

524
00:46:48,409 --> 00:46:50,525
What is it? What are you looking at?

525
00:46:51,689 --> 00:46:54,522
You think your kids
will jump over the wall?

526
00:47:16,169 --> 00:47:18,205
You were asking for it this time,
weren't you?

527
00:47:23,929 --> 00:47:25,885
See you in 30 days.

528
00:47:34,369 --> 00:47:37,759
Doctor, we're here to make
our relationship official.

529
00:47:37,929 --> 00:47:39,920
With all due respect.

530
00:47:40,089 --> 00:47:44,287
You understand, doctor.
So we can be more open.

531
00:47:44,609 --> 00:47:46,804
It's not the same with a rubber.

532
00:47:47,369 --> 00:47:50,759
There's not much sense,
her taking the test and not you.

533
00:47:51,089 --> 00:47:54,559
See? I told him, doctor,
but he's scared.

534
00:47:55,049 --> 00:47:56,277
Scared of what?

535
00:47:57,209 --> 00:47:59,848
-Scared of injections.
-Too Bad!

536
00:48:00,089 --> 00:48:02,967
-It's not that.
-So you're scared of getting married!

537
00:48:03,329 --> 00:48:03,569
Doctor, you're needed, urgently!

538
00:48:03,569 --> 00:48:05,799
Doctor, you're needed, urgently!

539
00:48:05,969 --> 00:48:06,924
Come on!

540
00:48:07,089 --> 00:48:08,886
Down you go, come on!

541
00:48:09,609 --> 00:48:11,088
It's all right now, doctor.

542
00:48:13,489 --> 00:48:14,968
I blacked out, doctor.

543
00:48:16,729 --> 00:48:18,447
Giving us all a fright, Zico?

544
00:48:19,849 --> 00:48:23,046
It's just as well, doctor.
Maybe he'll learn what drugs do.

545
00:48:23,329 --> 00:48:24,444
Tell him!

546
00:48:24,649 --> 00:48:27,083
What's there to tell? Drugs kill.

547
00:48:28,169 --> 00:48:30,239
-And you, who are you?
-That's Deusdete.

548
00:48:31,249 --> 00:48:33,160
We grew up together.

549
00:48:35,129 --> 00:48:36,482
You know, doctor...

550
00:48:37,089 --> 00:48:39,239
...one day my mother
didn't come home.

551
00:48:39,689 --> 00:48:41,088
I was left alone.

552
00:48:41,609 --> 00:48:42,598
I waited...

553
00:48:43,489 --> 00:48:44,683
...and waited...

554
00:48:46,569 --> 00:48:51,563
...until he and his sister, Franci,
came and took me to live with them.

555
00:49:01,449 --> 00:49:02,848
We grew up together.

556
00:49:05,769 --> 00:49:08,329
Wait!

557
00:49:29,369 --> 00:49:30,643
Come on, Zico!

558
00:49:45,169 --> 00:49:47,000
Wait, Zico!

559
00:50:12,929 --> 00:50:14,362
Zico!

560
00:50:17,729 --> 00:50:18,798
Help!

561
00:50:51,129 --> 00:50:52,801
Zico saved me, doctor.

562
00:50:54,049 --> 00:50:58,122
That's right. I've always
looked after him, from early on.

563
00:50:59,569 --> 00:51:02,288
Then you went the wrong way.

564
00:51:06,089 --> 00:51:11,322
What's wrong with buying some dope
and selling it to folks who like it?

565
00:51:12,329 --> 00:51:15,207
It wasn't even that much!
Another two years and I'm free.

566
00:51:15,609 --> 00:51:18,043
But I've never killed anyone.

567
00:51:19,289 --> 00:51:20,961
Unlike Deusdete here.

568
00:51:21,889 --> 00:51:23,527
What was your crime?

569
00:51:24,049 --> 00:51:25,641
Answer him, Deusdete!

570
00:51:30,809 --> 00:51:34,438
To tell you the truth,
he's not even a real criminal.

571
00:51:36,489 --> 00:51:38,445
So, what are you in here for?

572
00:51:40,209 --> 00:51:43,360
One night, I was at home...

573
00:51:44,289 --> 00:51:46,245
...when my sister arrived,
acting strange.

574
00:51:47,289 --> 00:51:48,517
Franci!

575
00:51:48,969 --> 00:51:51,722
What's wrong, Franci?
What happened?

576
00:51:51,929 --> 00:51:53,282
Franci!

577
00:52:00,649 --> 00:52:02,719
Franci, what happened?

578
00:52:04,489 --> 00:52:05,683
Open up, come on.

579
00:52:06,249 --> 00:52:08,126
What happened?

580
00:52:15,569 --> 00:52:17,082
What happened, Franci?

581
00:52:20,769 --> 00:52:22,885
What happened? Tell me.

582
00:52:23,849 --> 00:52:25,919
What happened?

583
00:52:28,769 --> 00:52:29,918
Tell me!

584
00:52:30,929 --> 00:52:32,647
There were two of them...

585
00:52:34,889 --> 00:52:36,242
...they grabbed me...

586
00:52:38,249 --> 00:52:40,001
...lifted my skirt.

587
00:52:42,889 --> 00:52:44,880
One said he wanted to suck me.

588
00:52:45,609 --> 00:52:48,806
-I told him to go suck his mother!
-What did they do to you?

589
00:52:48,969 --> 00:52:50,641
-They beat me.
-What else?

590
00:52:52,489 --> 00:52:53,524
What else?

591
00:52:53,689 --> 00:52:55,407
-That's all, Deusdete.
-Who was it?

592
00:52:55,569 --> 00:52:56,524
Who was it?

593
00:52:56,689 --> 00:52:59,362
-I just ran off!
-Did you know them?

594
00:53:07,889 --> 00:53:08,958
Hey, Zico!

595
00:53:12,329 --> 00:53:13,648
Deusdete?

596
00:53:13,929 --> 00:53:15,965
What are you doing here, man?

597
00:53:16,529 --> 00:53:17,928
I need to talk.

598
00:53:33,089 --> 00:53:34,602
Is Mother all right?

599
00:53:34,889 --> 00:53:36,686
It's not her.

600
00:53:37,329 --> 00:53:39,081
Some guys messed with Franci.

601
00:53:50,489 --> 00:53:51,888
What did they do to her?

602
00:53:52,769 --> 00:53:56,364
Nothing much, she says.
But I reported it to the cops anyway.

603
00:53:56,649 --> 00:54:00,324
The cops?! You think the cops
will do anything?!

604
00:54:00,489 --> 00:54:03,526
The problem is, the guys found out
and now they're after me.

605
00:54:07,449 --> 00:54:11,237
-Leave it to me. I'll sort them out.
-No, Zico. Not your way.

606
00:54:11,809 --> 00:54:12,958
I want--

607
00:54:16,809 --> 00:54:19,403
I just want a gun, to defend myself.

608
00:54:29,489 --> 00:54:30,842
Take your pick.

609
00:54:44,329 --> 00:54:47,241
Even with a gun, doctor, I never
thought anything would happen.

610
00:54:49,609 --> 00:54:55,206
But it was my destiny,
and theirs, when they found me.

611
00:55:03,369 --> 00:55:04,324
So!

612
00:55:05,289 --> 00:55:08,201
-Where's the stool pigeon off to?
-I'm not looking for a fight.

613
00:55:08,369 --> 00:55:11,122
-Let me go home.
-Sure thing...

614
00:55:11,369 --> 00:55:13,837
...but first we're going to caress you...

615
00:55:14,009 --> 00:55:16,204
...just like we did your little sister.

616
00:56:50,409 --> 00:56:51,558
Hey, man!

617
00:57:24,169 --> 00:57:25,761
Give me a Coke.

618
