I'll start losing respect around here.

642
00:59:15,849 --> 00:59:17,282
Cool it.

643
00:59:18,649 --> 00:59:22,005
I'll tell Ezequiel to get
the money from his family.

644
00:59:22,569 --> 00:59:26,357
If he doesn't pay,
you can go ahead.

645
00:59:36,289 --> 00:59:38,484
This man has already lost a lung...

646
00:59:38,649 --> 00:59:42,608
-...and the other's in pretty bad shape.
-Take the medicine, man, go on.

647
00:59:44,369 --> 00:59:46,564
See, doctor? He won't take it.

648
00:59:47,769 --> 00:59:49,646
What are you, a kid?
You won't get better...

649
00:59:49,809 --> 00:59:53,085
-...if you don't take it.
-Come on, that's right.

650
00:59:54,649 --> 00:59:55,638
That's it.

651
01:00:00,809 --> 01:00:01,764
Come on.

652
01:00:03,369 --> 01:00:04,358
Right.

653
01:00:08,649 --> 01:00:11,721
-Good.
-And on the outside? What did he do?

654
01:00:12,009 --> 01:00:14,159
We used to rob armored trucks.

655
01:00:14,329 --> 01:00:18,368
Just the two of us.
We planned everything. Remember?

656
01:00:18,609 --> 01:00:21,601
Doctor, we'd spend six months
just gathering information.

657
01:00:21,769 --> 01:00:24,044
We'd even make friends
with the guards' families.

658
01:00:24,209 --> 01:00:25,608
And that paid off?

659
01:00:25,929 --> 01:00:29,763
Sure, plenty. Although
we'd only use half the money.

660
01:00:29,969 --> 01:00:34,087
The rest we'd put aside
for a rainy day...

661
01:00:34,289 --> 01:00:36,325
...or to bribe the cops.

662
01:00:49,449 --> 01:00:50,564
It's coming.

663
01:01:20,529 --> 01:01:21,928
Stop!

664
01:01:24,249 --> 01:01:27,241
You going to sit there
on top of other people's money?

665
01:01:27,409 --> 01:01:29,923
If you don't come out it'll be
too bad for your widows.

666
01:01:30,089 --> 01:01:31,761
Open that door,
for Christ's sake!

667
01:01:34,049 --> 01:01:35,528
Come on, get out!

668
01:01:35,769 --> 01:01:38,078
So we paid off the others...

669
01:01:38,249 --> 01:01:41,127
...and each went his own way
back to the family.

670
01:01:43,289 --> 01:01:45,598
So anyway, Antonio,
what's on your mind?

671
01:01:48,809 --> 01:01:50,003
